(36, 1, '2016-01-18 23:12:06', '2016-01-18 23:12:06', 'MARKETPLACE TERMS AND CONDITIONS\r\n\r\nCare Nation Pty. Ltd. t/a CareNation ABN 62 601 420 535 (referred to as CareNation) provides an introductory service between care seekers who are seeking home care or health care services (Care Seeker) and home care professionals/care givers who are able to provide home care or health care services (Care Giver) (collectively, the Services). The Services are available on the CareNation website at www.carenation.com.au (Site).\r\n\r\n1. Contract\r\n\r\n(a) These Marketplace Terms and Conditions (Terms) form a binding legal agreement between CareNation, its directors, officers, employees, successors and assignees, and each person, organisation or entity using our Services (referred to as the User). By using the Site and Services, the User agrees to comply with and be legally bound by these Terms. Please read these Terms carefully. If there are any questions, the User is encouraged to contact CareNation at the contact details at the end of these Terms.\r\n\r\n(b) The User’s use of the Sites and/or Services indicates that:\r\n\r\n(i) he or she has had sufficient opportunity access the Terms and contact CareNation;\r\n\r\n(ii) he or she has read, accepted and will comply with the Terms;\r\n\r\n(iii) he or she has legal capacity to enter into a contract for sale; and\r\n\r\n(iv) he or she is eighteen (18) years or older.\r\n\r\nIf this is not correct, or if the User does not agree to these Terms, the User is not permitted to use any of the Services.\r\n\r\n(c) These Terms may be amended from time to time without prior notice. Use of our Services following any such amendments will be deemed to be confirmation that the User accepts those amendments. CareNation recommends that the User check the current Terms, before continuing use of the Services. CareNation’s agents, employees and third parties do not have authority to make changes to the Terms。\r\n\r\n(d) These Terms supplement and incorporate:\r\n\r\ni. The CareNation policies and terms and conditions, including without limitation the Website Terms of Use and Privacy Policy posted on the Site; and\r\n\r\nii. the Stripe Terms of Service.\r\n\r\n(e) CareNation’s Privacy Policy sets out how personal information is collected, used and protected. CareNation’s Website Terms of Use govern your use of the Site. These documents are available on the Site. Each User agrees to comply with the Privacy Policy regarding the handling of personal information and sensitive information provided by other Users.\r\n\r\n2. Introductory Service Only\r\n\r\n(a) The Site and the Services provide an online introductory platform for Care Seekers and Care Givers, through which Care Seekers will be able to: (i) view Care Giver’s Profiles; (ii) contact a Care Giver via the Site’s online messaging system to request the Care Giver’s home care\r\nor health care services (Care Giver Services); and (iii) post a job listing (Listing) requesting\r\nCare Giver Services and Care Givers will be able to: (i) view Listings; and (ii) contact a Care\r\nSeeker via the Site’s online messaging system to apply for a job set out in the Care Seeker’s\r\nListing.\r\n(b) A Care Seeker must set out all relevant information in a Listing, such as what type of Care\r\nGiver Services are required, when the Care Giver Services are required (time, dates and\r\nduration), the suburb and city in which the Care Giver Services will be required, the fee\r\noffered for the Care Giver Services, any requirements or preferences in respect of the Care\r\nGiver (e.g. they must have a valid working with children check or specific certifications or\r\nlicences) and any other terms and conditions applicable to the offer. A Care Giver is\r\nresponsible for its Listing and assumes all liability in relation to such.\r\n(c) Each User must create a profile as per information requested on the Site (Profile).\r\nCARE NATION PTY. LTD. T/A CARENATION ABN 62 601 420 535 MARKETPLACE TERMS AND CONDITIONS\r\n© LegalVision ILP Pty Ltd 2015 Confidential Page 2 of 12\r\n(d) Care Seekers cannot see the Profiles or Listings of other Care Seekers. Care Givers cannot\r\nsee the Profiles of other Care Givers or Care Seekers unless the Care Seeker has posted a\r\nListing.\r\n(e) Each User understands and agrees that the Site is an online introductory platform only, and\r\nthat CareNation’s responsibilities are limited to facilitating the availability of the Site and\r\nthe Services.\r\n(f) CareNation is not a party to any agreement entered into between a Care Seeker and a Care\r\nGiver. CareNation is not a referrer or booking agent, and provides no such related services.\r\nCareNation has no control over the conduct of the Care Seeker, Care Giver and any other\r\nusers of the Site and the Services. CareNation disclaims all liability in this regard, as set out\r\nin these Terms.\r\n(g) Any arrangement between a Care Seeker and a Care Giver is solely between the Care\r\nSeeker and the Care Giver. It is strictly and expressly not part of the User’s agreement with\r\nCareNation.\r\n3. Online Registration\r\n(a) Each User may only have one (1) account on the Site including a Profile (Account).\r\n(b) Basic information is required when registering on our Site either as a Care Seeker or Care\r\nGiver. Both Care Seekers and Care Givers are required to provide the requested\r\ninformation.\r\n(c) Each User agrees to provide accurate, current and complete information during the\r\nregistration process and to update such information to keep it accurate, current and\r\ncomplete. CareNation reserves the right to suspend or terminate any User’s Account and\r\nhis/her access to the Site and Services if any information provided to CareNation, proves to\r\nbe inaccurate, not current or incomplete.\r\n(d) Information that is created when a Care Seeker or Care Giver registers, and any subsequent\r\ninformation that is provided by the Care Seeker or Care Giver, is stored in servers within\r\nAustralia, which have their own security protocols, including firewalls and surveillance.\r\n(e) It is the User’s responsibility to keep its Account details and password confidential. The\r\nUser is liable for all activity on its Account, including purchases made using its account\r\ndetails. The User agrees that it will not disclose its password to any third party and that it\r\nwill take sole responsibility for any activities or actions under its Account, whether or not it\r\nhas authorised such activities or actions.\r\n(f) The User will immediately notify CareNation of any unauthorised use of its Account.\r\n(g) CareNation does not store any credit card information.\r\n4. Payments\r\n(a) Fees for Care Givers and Care Seekers will differ.\r\n(b) Care Givers are not required to pay any fees for registering on the Site or for the Services.\r\n(c) Care Seekers are required to pay, in advance, a periodic subscription fee as set out on the\r\nSite (Subscription Fee) to: (i) register on the Site; (ii) view Listings; and (iii) contact Care\r\nGivers via the Site’s online messaging system. Care Seekers acknowledge and agree that:\r\n(i) to maintain a subscription on the same periodic basis, payment of the then current\r\nSubscription Fee must be made to CareNation on the date on which the current\r\nsubscription expires (Renewal Date), via Stripe, a third party payment processor;\r\nand\r\n(ii) if CareNation does not receive payment in full, CareNation will attempt to contact\r\nthe User via email as soon as CareNation is aware of the payment failure.\r\nUntil payment is confirmed, the Account will be de-activated and the Care Seeker will not\r\nbe able to access the Services.\r\n(d) Each Care Seeker agrees that where a Subscription Fee is payable, payment will\r\nautomatically be deducted on the Renewal Date. If a Care Seeker wishes to cancel its\r\nsubscription or deactivate its Account, he or she must do so prior to the Renewal Date.\r\n(e) Each Care Seeker agrees to pay the Subscription Fees, in the currency specified on the Site,\r\nat the time that it applies for a subscription or on the Renewal Date, as applicable.\r\nCARE NATION PTY. LTD. T/A CARENATION ABN 62 601 420 535 MARKETPLACE TERMS AND CONDITIONS\r\n© LegalVision ILP Pty Ltd 2015 Confidential Page 3 of 12\r\n(f) Goods and Services Tax (GST) will be charged where applicable.\r\n(g) The Care Seeker must not pay, or attempt to pay the Subscription Fees through any\r\nfraudulent or unlawful means. If the Care Seeker’s payment is not able to be successfully\r\nprocessed then the request for a subscription or any of our subscription-based Services\r\nmay be cancelled.\r\n(h) In the absence of fraud or mistake, all payments made are final and the Care Seeker shall\r\nnot have the right to cancel its purchase for any reason and further each Care Seeker\r\nagrees to satisfy all such payments made.\r\n(i) CareNation’s pricing structure or payment methods may be amended from time to time at\r\nits sole discretion.\r\n5. Profiles\r\n(a) Care Givers who have created an Account must create a Profile. The Profile will be created\r\nfrom personal information that is provided to CareNation. A Care Giver’s Profile will only\r\ngo live on the Site once the Care Giver has provided Care Nation with a valid police\r\nbackground check and CareNation has reviewed and, at its discretion, approved such police\r\nbackground check. The Care Giver may either provide CareNation with an existing police\r\nbackground check (which must be less than 6 months old) or complete a new background\r\ncheck using Veritas, a third party service provider, whose details (including a link to their\r\nwebsite) can be found on the Site. CareNation is not responsible or liable for:\r\n(i) any inaccurate information or errors contained in the results of any background\r\nchecks performed by Veritas; or\r\n(ii) any loss or damage that occurs to a User, directly or indirectly, as a result of any\r\nbackground checks performed by Veritas.\r\n(b) Care Seekers who have created an Account must create a Profile. The Profile will be\r\ncreated from personal information that is provided to CareNation\r\n(c) Each User agrees to provide accurate, current and complete information during the\r\nregistration process, and to update its information to keep it accurate, current and\r\ncomplete.\r\n(d) Each User acknowledges and agrees that he or she is responsible for its Profile.\r\n(e) CareNation reserves the right, at any time and without prior notice, to remove or disable\r\naccess to any Account and/or Profile for any reason, including Accounts and/or Profiles that\r\nCareNation, in its sole discretion, considers to be objectionable for any reason, in violation\r\nof these Terms or otherwise harmful to the Site or Services.\r\n6. Care Givers\r\n(a) Care Givers can access the Site to view Listings and to contact Care Seekers via the Site’s\r\nonline messaging system to apply for jobs set out in Listings.\r\n(b) If a Care Giver contacts a Care Seeker and is asked to perform Care Giver Services for that\r\nCare Seeker, any agreement entered into is between the Care Seeker and Care Giver.\r\nCareNation is not a party to the agreement.\r\n(c) Each Care Giver acknowledges and agrees that they are not permitted to share the contact\r\ninformation of any Care Seekers with another User.\r\n(d) Each Care Giver represents and warrants that it has the necessary Australian Business\r\nNumber to provide its Care Giver Services and has made its own arrangements to ensure\r\nadequate insurance coverage (including, if applicable, public liability insurance) is effective\r\nand maintained in relation to the Care Giver Services.\r\n(e) Each Care Giver acknowledges and agrees that any communications entered into with a\r\nCare Seeker is at his or her own risk. CareNation does not provide the Care Seekers and\r\ncannot guarantee that these Care Seekers have genuine intentions.\r\n(f) Each Care Giver should report to CareNation, any activities or requests of Care Seekers\r\nwhich are, or which the Care Giver reasonably believes to be:\r\n(i) suspicious;\r\n(ii) inconsistent;\r\n(iii) illegal; or\r\nCARE NATION PTY. LTD. T/A CARENATION ABN 62 601 420 535 MARKETPLACE TERMS AND CONDITIONS\r\n© LegalVision ILP Pty Ltd 2015 Confidential Page 4 of 12\r\n(iv) likely to have a negative effect on the reputation of the Site, Services and/or User.\r\n(g) Each Care Giver represents and warrants that any content that it provides and Profile that\r\nit posts:\r\na. will not breach any agreements it has entered into with any third parties;\r\nb. will be in compliance with all applicable laws, tax requirements, and rules and regulations\r\nthat may apply to any Care Giver in its local area and country; and\r\nc. will not conflict with the rights of third parties.\r\n(h) For the avoidance of doubt, CareNation assumes no responsibility for a Care Giver’s\r\ncompliance with any applicable laws, rules and regulations.\r\n7. Care Seekers\r\n(a) Care Seekers with an Account can access the Site to view Care Givers’ Profiles, contact Care\r\nGivers via the Site’s online messaging system to request Care Giver Services and post\r\nListings requesting Care Giver Services.\r\n(c) Each Care Seeker acknowledges and agrees that whilst a Care Giver’s Profile will include a\r\npolice background check, CareNation cannot guarantee the completeness, accuracy or\r\nreliability of the police background check and that the Care Seeker must conduct its own\r\nbackground research in relation to the Care Giver.\r\n(c) If a Care Seeker requests Care Giver Services, any agreement entered into is between the\r\nCare Seeker and Care Giver. CareNation is not a party to the agreement.\r\n(d) Each Care Seeker acknowledges and agrees that they are not permitted to share the\r\ncontact information of any Care Givers with another User.\r\n(e) Each Care Seeker acknowledges and agrees that any communications entered into with a\r\nCare Giver are at his or her own risk. CareNation does not provide the Care Giver and\r\ncannot guarantee that these Care Givers have genuine intentions.\r\n(f) Each Care Seeker should report to CareNation, any activities or requests of Care Givers\r\nwhich are, or which the Care Seeker reasonably believes to be:\r\n(i) suspicious;\r\n(ii) inconsistent;\r\n(iii) illegal; or\r\n(iv) likely to have a negative effect on the reputation of the Site, Services and/or User.\r\n(g) Each Care Seeker represents and warrants that any content that they provide and any\r\nProfile and Listing that they post:\r\ni. will not breach any agreements it has entered into with any third parties;\r\nii. will be in compliance with all applicable laws, tax requirements, and rules and\r\nregulations that may apply to any Care Giver in its local area and country; and\r\niii. will not conflict with the rights of third parties.\r\n(h) For the avoidance of doubt, CareNation assumes no responsibility for a Care Seeker’s\r\ncompliance with any applicable laws, rules and regulations.\r\n8. Offers and Promotions\r\n(a) CareNation may, from time to time, make offers or promotions, which may be applicable to\r\nthe Services.\r\n(b) The conditions of such offers or promotions will be specified on the Site.\r\n(c) The User acknowledges and agrees that CareNation may, at its sole discretion, remove or\r\nextend any offers or promotions, and CareNation will not be responsible nor liable for any\r\npotential loss or damage which the User incurs as a result of the removal or extension of\r\nany offers or promotions.\r\n9. Ratings\r\n(a) Care Seekers and Care Givers who have entered into an agreement regarding the provision\r\nof Care Giver Services will be able to provide a star rating (Rating) of each other.\r\n(b) Once a Rating has been provided, the Rating cannot be reviewed and will be viewable to\r\nthe general public.\r\n(c) Ratings will remain viewable for as long as the Care Seeker or Care Giver has an active\r\nAccount.\r\nCARE NATION PTY. LTD. T/A CARENATION ABN 62 601 420 535 MARKETPLACE TERMS AND CONDITIONS\r\n© LegalVision ILP Pty Ltd 2015 Confidential Page 5 of 12\r\n(d) Each Care Seeker and Care Giver must provide true, fair and accurate information in any\r\nRating, and must not intentionally create any false or unfavourable Ratings which may\r\nunfairly negatively effect the reputation of the recipient of the Rating.\r\n(e) CareNation reserves the right to delete or amend a Rating at any time.\r\n(f) CareNation does not undertake to review each Rating and has no responsibility or liability\r\nfor any Ratings to the extent permissible by law.\r\n(g) CareNation will not be liable for any technical difficulties which result in any Ratings being\r\nviewed by any unintended person(s).\r\n10. Dispute Resolution\r\n(a) By using our Site and Services, each User agrees that any legal remedy or liability that he or\r\nshe may seek to obtain for actions or omission of a Care Seeker, Care Giver, or other third\r\nparty (including third party service providers), will be limited to a claim against the Care\r\nSeeker, Care Giver, or other third party (including third party service providers), who\r\ncaused harm to him or her. CareNation encourages Users to communicate directly with\r\nthe relevant Care Seeker, Care Giver or third party (including third party service providers)\r\nto resolve any disputes.\r\n(b) CareNation welcomes feedback from its Users. CareNation seeks to resolve concerns\r\nquickly and effectively. If any User has any feedback or question about the Services, please\r\ncontact any member of the staff.\r\n(c) If there are any complaints from a User, CareNation will aim to respond and provide a\r\nsuitable solution within 45 days. If a User is not satisfied with CareNation’s response, the\r\nUser and CareNation agree to the following dispute resolution procedure:\r\n(i) The complainant must tell the respondent in writing, the nature of the dispute,\r\nwhat outcome the complainant wants and what action the complainant thinks will\r\nsettle the dispute. The User and CareNation agree to meet in good faith to seek to\r\nresolve the dispute by agreement between them (Initial Meeting).\r\n(ii) If a resolution cannot be agreed upon at the Initial Meeting, either the User or\r\nCareNation may refer the matter to a mediator. If the User and CareNation cannot\r\nagree on who the mediator should be, the complainant will ask the Law Society of\r\nNew South Wales to appoint a mediator. The mediator will decide the time and\r\nplace for mediation. Each party to the dispute must attend the mediation in good\r\nfaith, to seek to resolve the dispute.\r\n(d) Any attempts made by a party to resolve a dispute pursuant to this clause are without\r\nprejudice to other rights or entitlements of either party under these Terms, by law or in\r\nequity.\r\n11. Cancellation of Subscription\r\n(a) A Care Seeker may cancel its subscription at any time by contacting CareNation using the\r\ncontact details set out below.\r\n(b) If a Care Seeker cancels its subscription, it will not receive a refund of any Subscription Fees\r\nalready paid. CareNation will not deduct any further Subscription Fees.\r\n12. Refund Policy\r\n(a) If CareNation terminates the Site or Services at any time and for any reason it may, at its\r\nsole discretion, offer a Care Seeker a full or partial refund of any Subscription Fees already\r\npaid, subject to reasonable deductions of CareNation’s administrative fees and third party\r\nservice provider charges.\r\n(b) Any cancellation or refund in respect of a Care Giver Service is strictly a matter between the\r\nCare Giver and the Care Seeker.\r\n13. Consumer Guarantees\r\n(a) Consumer legislation in Australia including the Australian Consumer Law (ACL) in the\r\nConsumer and Competition Act 2010 (Cth) provides consumers with guarantees that cannot\r\nbe excluded, restricted or modified (Rights). Similar consumer protection laws and\r\nregulations in other countries may provide consumers with similar guarantees.\r\nCARE NATION PTY. LTD. T/A CARENATION ABN 62 601 420 535 MARKETPLACE TERMS AND CONDITIONS\r\n© LegalVision ILP Pty Ltd 2015 Confidential Page 6 of 12\r\n(b) If the User is a consumer as defined in the ACL, the following notice applies to the User\r\nfrom CareNation: “We guarantee that the Services we supply to you are rendered with due\r\ncare and skill; fit for the purpose that we advertise, or that you have told us you are\r\nacquiring the Services for or for a result which you have told us you wish the Services\r\nachieve, unless we consider and disclose that this purpose is not achievable; and will be\r\nsupplied within a reasonable time. To the extent we are unable to exclude liability; our\r\ntotal liability for loss or damage you suffer or incur from our Services is limited to us resupplying\r\nthe Services to you, or, at our option, us refunding to you the amount you have\r\npaid us for the Services to which your claim relates.”\r\n12. Copyright and Intellectual Property\r\n(a) The Site contains material which is owned by or licensed to CareNation (or its affiliates\r\nand/or third party licensors as applicable), and is protected by Australian and international\r\nlaws, including but not limited to the trademarks, trade names, software, content, design,\r\nimages, graphics, layout, appearance, layout and look of the Site (Collective Content).\r\nCareNation and all material used in connection with the Site are unregistered or registered\r\ntrademarks of CareNation.\r\n(b) Intellectual Property includes all code, algorithms, copyright, fees, pricing, registered and\r\nunregistered, logos, slogans, designs, audio tracks, information, images, photographs,\r\npatents, know-how, trade secrets, ideas, methods, diagrams, drawings, databases, notes,\r\ndocuments, confidential information and any other proprietary or industrial rights relating\r\nto CareNation (in each case whether registered or unregistered or whether capable of\r\nregistration), together with any applications for registration and any rights to registration or\r\nrenewal of such rights anywhere in the world and whether created before or after the date\r\nof these Terms; goodwill in the business; trade, business company or organisation names;\r\ninternet domain names; Site content, images and layout. .\r\n(c) The User agrees that, as between the User and CareNation, CareNation owns all Intellectual\r\nProperty rights in the Site and Services, and that nothing in these Terms constitutes a\r\ntransfer of any Intellectual Property rights. CareNation owns the copyright which subsists\r\nin all creative and literary works displayed in the Site and Services. The Site and Services\r\nare protected by copyright, trademark, patent, trade secret, international treaties, laws and\r\nother proprietary rights, and also may have security components that protect digital\r\ninformation only as authorised by CareNation or the owner of the content.\r\n(d) Other trademarks, service marks, graphics and logos used in connection with the Site and\r\nServices are the trademarks of their respective owners (collectively Third Party Marks).\r\n(e) CareNation’s Intellectual Property and Third Party Marks may not be copied, imitated or\r\nused, in whole or in part, without the prior written permission of CareNation or the\r\napplicable trademark holder.\r\n(f) Users of the Site do not obtain any interest or licence in the Intellectual Property or Third\r\nParty Marks without the prior written permission of CareNation or the applicable\r\ntrademark holder. Users may not do anything which interferes with or breaches the\r\nIntellectual Property rights.\r\n13. User Licence\r\n(a) Subject to these Terms, CareNation grants the User a personal, non-exclusive, nontransferable,\r\nlimited and revocable licence to use the Site and Services for its own personal\r\na