mpleteness,\r\naccuracy or reliability of the police background check;\r\niii. meet for the first time in a safe public place, during daylight hours;\r\niv. do not consume any alcohol at the meeting;\r\nv. take a friend or family member with you to the meeting;\r\nvi. if you are a Care Giver, provide a friend or family member with full details of where\r\nyou will be providing the Care Giver Services;\r\nvii. if you are a Care Seeker, provide a friend or family member with full details of your\r\nCare Giver; and\r\nviii. do not share or exchange any personal information other than as reasonably\r\nnecessary for the Care Giver to provide the Care Giver Services and/or financial\r\ndetails unless reasonably necessary to pay for the Care Giver Services.\r\nThe above is a guideline only; it is not advice. Each User is solely responsible for ensuring\r\nits safety when meeting up with other Users and excludes CareNation from all liability in\r\nthis regard.\r\n(f) CareNation is not responsible for the quality of services provided by third party service\r\nproviders (including Veritas and Stripe) and assumes no liability for such. Any recourse a\r\nUser has in respect of the services of a third party service provider is against the third party\r\nservice provider directly.\r\n(g) By using the Site or Services, the User agrees that any legal remedy or liability that it seeks\r\nto obtain for actions or omissions of other Care Seekers or Care Givers or other third parties\r\nwill be limited to a claim against the Care Seeker or Care Giver or other third party who\r\ncaused it harm. CareNation encourages the User to communicate directly with the relevant\r\nCare Seeker or Care User on the Site and Services regarding any communications or\r\narrangements made between them and to resolve any dispute between them.\r\n(h) To the fullest extent allowable under applicable law, CareNation disclaims all warranties,\r\nrepresentations and conditions, whether express or implied, inclu